    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="872"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d872">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/417.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation.</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 16, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s July 12. Liberian Government will place monthly sums to Clark’s
                    credit provided assurance is given that no interest on outstanding loans will be
                    required after June 30.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crum.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
